This is a really neat idea for automatically scrolling through sheet music, using your phone, whilst one plays an instrument. Just a few small but important deficiencies. Needs the ability to set repeats and a coda, set tempo changes and time signature changes at the beginning of a bar. Also, optionally skip or reduce the count in on playback (can be annoying with slow scores). Also dynamically adjust position or tempo during playback (for during practice, wanting to repeat a bar / section).

content: Only thing I can hear is metronome. Edit: I was mistsken about purpose of this app. It is just for reading notes, not playing. If you play instrument, you can use it to scroll notes for you. It is good idea. Sorry for bad review earlier.
replyContent:
Please read the description carefully. This app doesn't play the music score. It turns your music scores into a stripe, and makes it scroll at your favourite tempo. In this way you can carry all of your music sheets in your smartphone, and play them wherever you like.

content: This is an exceptional app that shows a bar at a time, with metronome.
